#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.143"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.143:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:0.2"
msgid "15. Tikaṇḍakīvagga "
msgstr "15. At Tikaṇḍakī "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.143:0.3"
msgid "143. Sārandadasutta "
msgstr "143. At Sārandada "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.143:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Vesālī for alms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena pañcamattānaṃ licchavisatānaṃ sārandade cetiye sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi: "
msgstr "Now at that time around five hundred Licchavis were sitting together at the Sārandada shrine, and this discussion came up among them, "

msgctxt "an5.143:1.4"
msgid "“pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“The appearance of five treasures is rare in the world. "

msgctxt "an5.143:1.5"
msgid "Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.143:1.6"
msgid "Hatthiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, assaratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, maṇiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, itthiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, gahapatiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "The elephant-treasure, the horse-treasure, the jewel-treasure, the woman-treasure, and the householder-treasure. "

msgctxt "an5.143:1.7"
msgid "Imesaṃ pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "The appearance of these five treasures is rare in the world.” "

# NOTE: reading pesesum
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.168, sc2
#. VAR: ṭhapesuṃ → pesesuṃ (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an5.143:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho te licchavī magge purisaṃ ṭhapesuṃ: "
msgstr "Then those Licchavis sent a man out on to the road, saying, "

#. VAR: yadā tvaṃ → yathā tvaṃ (si, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.143:2.2"
msgid "“yadā tvaṃ, ambho purisa, passeyyāsi bhagavantaṃ, atha amhākaṃ āroceyyāsī”ti. "
msgstr "“Mister, please tell us when you see the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:2.3"
msgid "Addasā kho so puriso bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ; "
msgstr "That man saw the Buddha coming off in the distance. "

msgctxt "an5.143:2.4"
msgid "disvāna yena te licchavī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te licchavī etadavoca: "
msgstr "He went to the Licchavis and said, "

msgctxt "an5.143:2.5"
msgid "“ayaṃ so, bhante, bhagavā gacchati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho; "
msgstr "“Sirs, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha is coming. "

msgctxt "an5.143:2.6"
msgid "yassadāni kālaṃ maññathā”ti. "
msgstr "Please go at your convenience.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.143:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho te licchavī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho te licchavī bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then those Licchavis went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him, "

#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.143:4.1"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante, yena sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Please go to the Sārandada shrine, out of compassion.” "

msgctxt "an5.143:4.2"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā te licchavī etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha went up to the Sārandada shrine, where he sat on the seat spread out, and said to the Licchavis, "

msgctxt "an5.143:4.4"
msgid "“kāya nuttha, licchavī, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti? "
msgstr "“Licchavis, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was unfinished?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:4.5"
msgid "“Idha, bhante, amhākaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi: "
msgstr "“Well, Master Gotama, this discussion came up among us while we were sitting together: "

msgctxt "an5.143:4.6"
msgid "‘pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "‘The appearance of five treasures is rare in the world. …’” "

msgctxt "an5.143:4.7"
msgid "Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.143:4.8"
msgid "Hatthiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, assaratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, maṇiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, itthiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, gahapatiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.143:4.9"
msgid "Imesaṃ pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin’”ti. "
msgstr " "

# NOTE: Vo is probably not the right reading, but is implied anyway.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.169, sc5
#. VAR: Kāmādhimuttānaṃ vata bho licchavīnaṃ → kāmādhimuttānaṃ vata vo licchavīnaṃ (bj) | kāmādhimuttānaṃ vata vo licchavī (s1-3) | kāmādhimuttānaṃva vo licchavī (?)
msgctxt "an5.143:5.1"
msgid "“Kāmādhimuttānaṃ vata bho licchavīnaṃ kāmaṃyeva ārabbha antarākathā udapādi. "
msgstr "“You Licchavis are so fixated on sensual pleasures, that’s the only discussion that came up! "

msgctxt "an5.143:5.2"
msgid "Pañcannaṃ, licchavī, ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "Licchavis, the appearance of five treasures is rare in the world. "

msgctxt "an5.143:5.3"
msgid "Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:5.4"
msgid "Tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "The appearance of a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:5.5"
msgid "tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desetā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "A person who explains the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: viññātā → viññātassa (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.143:5.6"
msgid "tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "A person who understands the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:5.7"
msgid "tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā dhammānudhammappaṭipanno puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "A person who practices in line with the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:5.8"
msgid "kataññū katavedī puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "A person who is grateful and thankful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.143:5.9"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, licchavī, pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "The appearance of these five treasures is rare in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.143:5.10"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

